name: Spy Detected!
description:
You are given an array 
    a
 consisting of 
    n
 (
    n 
    ≥ 3
)
positive integers. It is known that in this array, all the numbers except one
are the same (for example, in the array 
    [4, 11, 4, 4]
 all numbers except
one are equal to 
    4
). Print the index of the element that does not equal
others. The numbers in the array are numbered from one. Input The first line
contains a single integer 
    t
 (
    1 
    ≤ t 
    ≤ 100
). Then 
    t

test cases follow. The first line of each test case contains a single integer

    n
 (
    3 
    ≤ n 
    ≤ 100
) — the length of the array 
    a
. The
second line of each test case contains 
    n
 integers 
    a_1, a_2, 
    …,
    a_n
 (
    1 
    ≤ a_i 
    ≤ 100
). It is guaranteed that all the numbers
except one in the 
    a
 array are the same. Output For each test case,
output a single integer — the index of the element that is not equal to
others. Example Input 4 4 11 13 11 11 5 1 4 4 4 4 10 3 3 3 3 10 3 3 3 3 3 3 20
20 10 Output 2 1 5 3
